Recruiters distribute tote bags filled with branded notebooks and pens, while the lively atmosphere is enhanced by the aroma of coffee and catered snacks. Alumni volunteers provide pep talks in the lounge, and career counselors assist students, emphasizing the importance of eye contact during conversations. Workshops on networking etiquette and a panel on technical interview preparation occur in an adjoining classroom. Attendees utilize kiosks to upload resumes and compare swag items, while interview sign-up sheets quickly fill up as the event nears its conclusion.

The aroma of coffee and catered snacks fills the air as students line up, comparing swag items like water bottles and phone chargers while clutching resumes in branded folders. Recruiters distribute tote bags containing branded notebooks and pens. Career counselors assist students, encouraging them to maintain eye contact, and international students seek advice on visa sponsorship. An alumni panel discusses technical interview preparation, and a startup founder hosts a lunchtime pitch session. Throughout the day, workshops on networking etiquette occur nearby, as career center staff log attendance metrics and track interview sign-ups amidst the lively atmosphere of conversations and interactions between attendees and recruiters.
